This is a serious data integrity issue that causes silent data corruption.

The bug occurs because the constructor incorrectly reuses the sparse index and values from the original array without recomputing them when the fill_value changes. Values equal to the old fill_value are stored implicitly, and when the fill_value changes, these implicit values are misinterpreted as the new fill_value.
